---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro'

const platformLogos = [
  'google-business-profile', 'linkedin', 'youtube', 'bing', 'trustpilot',
  'github', 'medium', 'substack', 'reddit', 'quora', 'clutch', 'blogger',
  'apple-podcasts', 'spotify-podcasts', 'facebook', 'instagram', 'x-twitter',
  'threads', 'pinterest', 'wordpress', 'crunchbase', 'goodfirms', 'wikidata',
  'companies-house', 'google-scholar', 'product-hunt', 'devto', 'hashnode',
  'tumblr', 'flipboard', 'listen-notes', 'capterra', 'g2', 'stack-overflow',
  'glassdoor', 'angellist', 'google-my-maps', 'google-dataset-search',
  'apple-business-connect', 'google-ecosystem'
]
---
<Layout
  title="Rank4AI – UK AI Search Agency | AI Search Visibility"
  description="UK AI search agency focused on improving visibility and recommendation likelihood across ChatGPT, Claude, Gemini, Perplexity, Copilot and Google AI."
>

<!-- HERO -->
<section class="pt-24 pb-20 px-10 max-md:px-6 text-center">
  <div class="max-w-[800px] mx-auto">
    <p class="text-[13px] font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.1em] text-accent mb-7">UK AI Search Agency</p>
    <h1 class="mb-6">Get Your Business Recommended by AI Search</h1>

    <img src="/images/content/ai-search-signals.svg" alt="AI search visibility signals" class="w-full rounded-xl mb-8 mt-6" loading="lazy">
    <div class="platform-bar dark justify-center mb-7">
      <span class="platform"><span class="icon icon-chatgpt">G</span> ChatGPT</span>
      <span class="platform"><span class="icon icon-claude">C</span> Claude</span>
      <span class="platform"><span class="icon icon-gemini">G</span> Gemini</span>
      <span class="platform"><span class="icon icon-perplexity">P</span> Perplexity</span>
      <span class="platform"><span class="icon icon-copilot">C</span> Copilot</span>
      <span class="platform"><span class="icon icon-googleai">G</span> Google AI</span>
    </div>
    <p class="text-lg text-text-muted leading-relaxed max-w-[580px] mx-auto mb-10">When someone asks an AI platform to recommend a business in your category, one or two get mentioned. The rest do not exist.</p>
    <a href="/free-audit/" class="cta-primary">Get a Free AI Search Visibility Audit &rarr;</a>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 3 STAT BOXES -->
<section class="pb-16 px-10 max-md:px-6">
  <div class="max-w-[700px] mx-auto grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
    <div class="bg-white-pure border border-border rounded-xl p-6 text-center">
      <div class="font-display text-4xl text-teal leading-none mb-1.5">1,400+</div>
      <div class="text-[13px] text-text-muted">UK businesses audited</div>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-white-pure border border-border rounded-xl p-6 text-center">
      <div class="font-display text-4xl text-teal leading-none mb-1.5">6</div>
      <div class="text-[13px] text-text-muted">AI platforms tested</div>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-white-pure border border-border rounded-xl p-6 text-center">
      <div class="font-display text-4xl text-teal leading-none mb-1.5">77%</div>
      <div class="text-[13px] text-text-muted">of UK SMEs sending confusing signals to AI</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- SIGNAL BANNER -->
<section class="bg-off-white border-t border-b border-border py-12 px-10 max-md:px-6 overflow-hidden">
  <h2 class="text-center text-teal !text-2xl md:!text-3xl max-w-[600px] mx-auto mb-3">We build across 85+ platforms and sources</h2>
  <p class="text-center text-sm text-text-muted max-w-[700px] mx-auto mb-8">Entity verification. Authority. Trust. Citations. Technical credibility. Distribution. Six signal types across the platforms AI systems use to decide who to recommend.</p>
  <div class="flex justify-center gap-6 flex-wrap mb-8">
    {['Entity Verification', 'Authority', 'Trust', 'Citations', 'Technical Credibility', 'Distribution'].map(type => (
      <span class="text-xs font-semibold text-teal px-3.5 py-1.5 border border-border rounded-full bg-white">{type}</span>
    ))}
  </div>
  <div class="scroll-track-wrap">
    <div class="scroll-track">
      {[...platformLogos, ...platformLogos].map(logo => (
        <img src={`/images/${logo}.png`} alt={logo} title={logo} loading="lazy">
      ))}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ANSWER BLOCK -->
<section class="reveal container-narrow py-24 border-b border-border">
  <div class="section-tag">The question every business is asking</div>
  <h2 class="mb-6">How do I get my business recommended on ChatGPT, Claude and Google AI?</h2>
  <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">Rank4AI is a UK AI search agency. We get your business recommended by ChatGPT, Claude, Gemini, Perplexity, Copilot and Google AI.</p>
  <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">This work is sometimes described as AI SEO, GEO or AIO. These terms all describe the same challenge: appearing inside AI-generated answers rather than traditional search result lists.</p>
  <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">We do not offer traditional SEO retainers or PPC services. Our focus is entirely on AI driven search recommendations, not Google ranking positions.</p>
  <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">Google traffic is collapsing. Organic clicks down 17%, paid down 68%. That traffic moved to AI search. We help you get recommended when buyers ask who to trust.</p>
  <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5"><span class="highlight">The result? More traffic, more enquiries, and stronger market presence.</span></p>
  <p class="mt-6"><a href="/free-audit/" class="link">Get a Free AI Search Visibility Audit &rarr;</a></p>
</section>

<!-- 3 STEPS -->
<section class="reveal container py-24 border-b border-border">
  <div class="section-tag">How It Works</div>
  <h2 class="text-center mb-16">Three steps. No jargon.</h2>
  <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
    {[
      { num: '01', title: 'Audit', desc: 'We test your visibility across ChatGPT, Claude, Gemini, Perplexity, Copilot and Google AI. You get a personalised report.' },
      { num: '02', title: 'Report', desc: 'A clear breakdown – what AI sees, what it misses, and what to fix first. No jargon. No waffle.' },
      { num: '03', title: 'Action', desc: 'We build it for you, or give you the roadmap to do it yourself. Your call. You choose the pace.' },
    ].map(step => (
      <div class="text-center relative">
        <div class="font-display text-5xl text-teal opacity-10 leading-none mb-3">{step.num}</div>
        <h3 class="!text-xl text-teal mb-2.5">{step.title}</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-text-muted leading-relaxed">{step.desc}</p>
      </div>
    ))}
  </div>
</section>

<!-- SEARCH HAS CHANGED -->
<section class="reveal container-narrow py-24">
  <div class="section-tag">The Shift</div>
  <h2 class="mb-6">Search has changed</h2>
  <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">Traditional search showed a list of websites. Users clicked through and chose.</p>
  <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">AI works differently. It gives a single answer. That answer is not based on Google rankings. It is based on which business the AI system <span class="highlight">understands clearly, trusts, and can confidently recommend.</span></p>
  <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed">In our UK testing, the overlap between strong Google rankings and AI answers is consistently low. Businesses on page one of Google are regularly absent from AI responses entirely.</p>
</section>

<div class="border-t border-border"></div>

<!-- HOW AI DECIDES -->
<section class="reveal container-narrow py-24">
  <div class="section-tag">How AI Decides</div>
  <h2 class="mb-6">AI does not rely on your website alone</h2>
  <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">AI platforms build a picture of your business from everywhere it appears online. Your website. Your directories. Your reviews. Your press mentions. Your professional listings. Your editorial coverage.</p>
  <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5"><span class="highlight">One voice is weak evidence. Many consistent voices from independent sources are strong evidence.</span></p>
  <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed">A business that appears consistently across trusted sources – with the same clear description of what it does everywhere – gets recommended. A business that only exists on its own website, or describes itself differently in different places, gets skipped.</p>
</section>

<!-- STATS & FACTS -->
<section class="reveal teal-section py-20 px-10 max-md:px-6">
  <div class="max-w-[1200px] mx-auto">
    <div class="section-tag section-tag-light">UK AI Visibility Research</div>
    <h2 class="!text-text-light mb-3">What we found when we audited 1,400+ UK business websites</h2>
    <p class="text-text-light-muted mb-12 max-w-[600px] text-base">Original research data. No other AI search agency has this.</p>
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
      {[
        { stat: '77%', desc: 'of UK business websites are giving AI conflicting information about what they do' },
        { stat: '53%', desc: 'have a homepage heading so vague that AI cannot tell what the business actually does' },
        { stat: '44%', desc: 'have no way for AI to identify who they are from the code behind their website' },
        { stat: '23%', desc: 'are accidentally invisible to at least one major AI platform and do not know it' },
        { stat: '62%', desc: 'say something different about themselves in three different places on their own website' },
        { stat: '13%', desc: 'have set up the one file that lets them talk directly to AI search platforms' },
      ].map(item => (
        <div class="stat-card-teal">
          <div class="font-display text-5xl text-accent-bright leading-none mb-2">{item.stat}</div>
          <div class="text-sm text-text-light-muted leading-snug">{item.desc}</div>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>
    <p class="text-center mt-8"><a href="/research/uk-ai-visibility-stats/" class="text-accent-bright font-medium text-[15px] hover:underline">See all 26 research stats &rarr;</a></p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- WHAT WE BUILD -->
<section class="reveal container py-24">
  <div class="section-tag">What We Build</div>
  <h2 class="mb-4">The connected presence that earns AI trust</h2>
  <p class="text-text-muted mb-12 max-w-[800px] text-[17px] leading-relaxed">We build the full picture AI needs to recommend your business. Not just content. Not just your website. The entire digital footprint – structured, connected, and consistent across every source AI platforms draw from.</p>
  <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-5">
    {[
      { title: 'Entity Verification', desc: 'Confirming your business exists and is real. Legal registration. Governance records. Industry standards. Institutional trust signals.' },
      { title: 'Authority Signals', desc: 'Content that demonstrates structured expertise. Guides. Research. Answers to the questions your customers actually ask.' },
      { title: 'Trust Signals', desc: 'Reviews. Ratings. Reputation platforms. Independent users confirming your business does what it says.' },
      { title: 'Citation Signals', desc: 'Press mentions. Editorial coverage. Community references. PR citations. Third-party sources independently referencing your business.' },
      { title: 'Technical Credibility', desc: 'Your web presence structured so AI can read it. Crawler access. Structured data. The technical foundations for AI extraction.' },
      { title: 'Distribution Signals', desc: 'Publishing platforms. Video. Podcasts. Professional listings. The breadth that extends your entity footprint.' },
    ].map(card => (
      <div class="card-teal-border">
        <h3 class="!text-lg text-teal mb-2.5">{card.title}</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-text-muted leading-relaxed">{card.desc}</p>
      </div>
    ))}
  </div>
</section>

<!-- BRAND EQUITY -->
<section class="reveal container-narrow py-24 border-t border-border">
  <div class="section-tag">The Bigger Picture</div>
  <h2 class="mb-6">Building digital brand equity</h2>
  <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">This is not a ChatGPT trick. It is building genuine digital brand equity – a clearly understood business, with clear messaging, a strong website, and a connected digital footprint across the sources AI systems already trust.</p>
  <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">Established brands already appear in AI answers. Not because they did AI work – but because they accumulated this over years. Directory listings. Press mentions. Consistent presence everywhere. AI systems have seen them and trust them.</p>
  <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5"><span class="highlight">We engineer deliberately what they accumulated passively. The mechanism is the same. The timeline is different.</span></p>
  <p class="font-display text-2xl text-teal mt-8">Presence. Consistency. Confidence. Inclusion.</p>
</section>

<!-- AI ENDORSEMENT -->
<section class="reveal bg-off-white border-t border-b border-border py-20 px-10 max-md:px-6">
  <div class="max-w-[1200px] mx-auto">
    <div class="section-tag">Independent Validation</div>
    <h2 class="mb-2">What AI platforms said about our methodology</h2>
    <p class="text-text-muted mb-10">We asked ChatGPT, Claude and Perplexity to evaluate our AI Search Audit methodology. Here is what they returned:</p>
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
      {[
        { platform: 'ChatGPT', quote: 'This is the most comprehensive AI search report in existence.' },
        { platform: 'Claude', quote: 'Shows the signal structures clearly and consistently.' },
        { platform: 'Perplexity', quote: 'Matches how we interpret clarity and identity patterns.' },
      ].map(endorsement => (
        <div class="bg-white-pure border border-border rounded-xl p-7">
          <div class="text-[13px] font-bold text-teal uppercase tracking-wide mb-3">{endorsement.platform}</div>
          <p class="text-sm text-text-muted leading-relaxed italic">"{endorsement.quote}"</p>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- TESTIMONIALS -->
<section class="reveal container py-24">
  <div class="section-tag">What Clients Say</div>
  <h2 class="mb-12">Working with Rank4AI</h2>
  <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
    <div class="testimonial-card">
      <p>"This team truly understands AI search and what it means for modern marketing. They helped us optimize our content and strategy for AI powered discovery, resulting in measurable gains in visibility and engagement. Their approach is smart, forward thinking, and grounded in real performance."</p>
      <div class="author">Rhys Davies – CEO, Blackthorne Consulting</div>
    </div>
    <div class="testimonial-card">
      <p>"We knew AI search was going to be a big shift. The number of people starting to look for services through tools like ChatGPT is rising fast, and it felt important for us to understand this properly and build a solid baseline early on. What stood out straight away was how down to earth the team are. They clearly know their stuff, but they also take the time to explain what is being done and why it matters. Unlike traditional agencies, we were not passed down to juniors. We worked directly with senior people throughout the process. It was a breath of fresh air."</p>
      <div class="author">Rishi Bansropun – Managing Director, RB Financial</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<div class="border-t border-border"></div>

<!-- WHY NOW -->
<section class="reveal container-narrow py-24">
  <div class="section-tag">The Window</div>
  <h2 class="mb-6">Why now matters</h2>
  <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">The businesses that build AI trust now will be extremely difficult to displace. AI confidence compounds over time. Each month of consistent signals makes the position more stable.</p>
  <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed">Most competitors are not thinking about this yet. <span class="highlight">Consistency compounds. Instability resets what has been built.</span> This is the window.</p>
</section>

<div class="border-t border-border"></div>

<!-- FIVE SIGNALS -->
<section class="reveal container py-24">
  <div class="section-tag">The Five Signal Model</div>
  <h2 class="mb-4">How AI forms confidence in your business</h2>
  <p class="text-text-muted mb-12">AI systems evaluate businesses through five signal layers. When all five are strong, the business gets recommended. When any one is weak, confidence drops.</p>
  <div class="grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-5 gap-4">
    {[
      { name: 'Identity Clarity', q: 'Can AI clearly understand what your business is, what category it belongs to, and what it should not be confused with?' },
      { name: 'Subject Authority', q: 'Does AI associate your business with the right topics, questions and expertise?' },
      { name: 'Meaning Architecture', q: 'Can AI read, understand and interpret your website structure, page layouts, internal linking and technical foundations?' },
      { name: 'Ecosystem Validation', q: 'Do third-party platforms and public sources describe your business consistently?' },
      { name: 'Signal Consistency', q: 'Do your older content and signals align with your current positioning, or do they contradict it?' },
    ].map(signal => (
      <div class="signal-card">
        <h3>{signal.name}</h3>
        <p>{signal.q}</p>
      </div>
    ))}
  </div>
</section>

<div class="border-t border-border"></div>

<!-- WHO WE HELP -->
<section class="reveal container py-24">
  <div class="section-tag">Who We Help</div>
  <h2 class="mb-8">AI visibility for your sector</h2>
  <div class="grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-3 gap-3 mb-6">
    {['Professional Services', 'Ecommerce', 'Local Business', 'SaaS', 'B2B', 'Retail'].map(sector => (
      <a href={`/who-we-help/${sector.toLowerCase().replace(' ', '-')}/`} class="bg-off-white border border-border rounded-xl px-6 py-5 text-[15px] font-medium text-text hover:bg-teal hover:text-text-light hover:border-teal transition-all">
        {sector}
      </a>
    ))}
  </div>
  <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-5 text-sm">
    {['London', 'Manchester', 'Birmingham', 'Leeds', 'Bristol', 'Essex', 'Colchester'].map(city => (
      <a href={`/who-we-help/${city.toLowerCase()}/`} class="text-text-muted hover:text-teal transition-colors">{city}</a>
    ))}
  </div>
</section>

<!-- FAQ -->
<section class="reveal container-narrow py-24 border-t border-border">
  <div class="section-tag">Common Questions</div>
  <h2 class="mb-10">Frequently asked</h2>
  {[
    { q: 'What is AI search visibility?', a: 'AI search visibility is whether AI platforms like ChatGPT, Claude, Gemini, Perplexity, Copilot and Google AI can find, understand and recommend your business when someone asks a relevant question. It is different from SEO – AI systems recommend businesses, not web pages.' },
    { q: 'Is this the same as SEO?', a: 'No. SEO ranks pages in search results. AI search visibility determines whether AI platforms recommend your business in generated answers. Different systems, different signals. In our testing, businesses on page one of Google are regularly absent from AI responses entirely.' },
    { q: 'Which AI platforms do you cover?', a: 'ChatGPT, Claude, Gemini, Perplexity, Copilot and Google AI. Each sources information differently and requires a different mix of signals. We test and build across all six.' },
    { q: 'Do you need to work on my website?', a: 'Not necessarily. Our ecosystem services build your AI presence entirely outside your website – we do not touch your site, your code or your current setup. For businesses that want us working on the website directly, we offer full agency engagements. The audit tells us which approach is right.' },
    { q: 'How long does it take to see results?', a: 'Initial effects appear within weeks. AI confidence builds and compounds over months as signals become more consistent across more trusted sources. This is infrastructure, not a campaign.' },
    { q: 'How much does it cost?', a: 'Every engagement starts with an AI Visibility Audit. Ecosystem services start from £800 per month. Full agency services are scoped individually following the audit. See our full pricing on the Work With Us page.' },
  ].map(faq => (
    <div class="faq-item">
      <div class="faq-q">{faq.q}</div>
      <div class="faq-a">{faq.a}</div>
    </div>
  ))}
</section>

<!-- FINAL CTA -->
<section class="bg-off-white border-t border-border text-center py-24 px-10 max-md:px-6">
  <h2 class="mb-4">Find out if AI can see your business</h2>
  <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted mb-10 max-w-[500px] mx-auto">Every engagement starts with an audit across all six AI platforms. We test how AI currently interprets your business, identify the gaps, and tell you exactly where to start.</p>
  <a href="/free-audit/" class="cta-primary">Get a Free AI Search Visibility Audit &rarr;</a>
</section>

